The details of the agreement, including the financial terms and any specific implications of this partnership, were not disclosed. However, this strategic deal showcases ECARX's commitment to expanding its presence in the market and potentially accelerating its growth trajectory.

data.description: In Boca Raton, Florida, Celsius Holdings, Inc. (Nasdaq: CELH) is set to announce its financial results for the third quarter of 2025 on Thursday, November 6, 2025, before the market opens.

data.title: Chris Sultemeier joins ArcBest Board of Directors on Oct. 29, 2025. Dr. Craig E. Philip to retire in Jan. 2026.
data.description: Chris Sultemeier has been appointed to the ArcBest Board of Directors in Fort Smith, Arkansas, with his term commencing on October 29, 2025. Concurrently, Dr. Craig E. Philip will be stepping down from the board in January 2026.

data.title: Dexcom stock falls 15% due to cautious outlook despite solid Q3 report. Investors concerned.
data.description: The third-quarter report from Dexcom, a leading company in the medical technology sector, was generally positive. However, the company's stock faced a significant setback on Friday as it plummeted by 15%. This drop was primarily attributed to Dexcom's outlook for the future, which was perceived as overly cautious by investors and analysts. Despite posting solid financial results for the quarter, the company's stock performance was overshadowed by concerns raised due to the conservative outlook. This development was highlighted in a recent article published by Investor's Business Daily.

data.title: Wesco International stock earns 87 RS Rating, showing strong performance.
data.description: Wesco International's Relative Strength Rating has surged to over 80. The company's stock has earned an impressive rating of 87 RS. This development indicates a strong performance compared to other stocks in the market.

data.title: Roku's Cl A stock receives Relative Strength Rating upgrade indicating improved technical performance.
data.description: Roku Cl A has seen a boost in its Relative Strength Rating, indicating improved technical performance. This upgrade comes as good news for investors, as it suggests positive momentum for the stock. The latest rating upgrade reflects a growing strength in Roku Cl A's performance.

data.title: XRP rewards debit card re-introduced by Uphold in the U.S., providing up to 6% rewards as crypto payments rise in popularity.
data.description: Uphold has announced the re-launch of its XRP rewards debit card to the United States market. This move comes as cryptocurrency payments are becoming increasingly popular among both consumers and merchants. The card offers rewards of up to 6% on purchases made with crypto. This initiative aims to capitalize on the growing interest in digital currencies, with the potential to earn significant rewards for users.

data.title: TeraWulf Inc. closes $1.025B 0.00% Convertible Notes offering to qualified institutional buyers.
data.description: TeraWulf Inc., a prominent owner and operator of low-carbon digital infrastructure based in EASTON, Md., recently concluded its offering of 0.00% Convertible Senior Notes due 2032. The offering, completed on Oct. 31, 2025, involved a total of $1.025 billion in aggregate principal amount of notes. This amount comprises $125 million from additional notes issued through an option granted to the initial purchasers. The offering was conducted privately with qualified institutional buyers under Rule 144A of the Securities Act of 1933. TeraWulf Inc. operates under the ticker symbol "WULF" on the Nasdaq stock exchange.

data.title: Allbirds appoints Lily Yan Hughes as independent director, effective Oct 31, 2025. She is former global S&P 500 and Fortune 100 exec.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, Allbirds, Inc. (NASDAQ: BIRD), a renowned global lifestyle brand focusing on sustainable materials for product innovation, disclosed the addition of Lily Yan Hughes as an independent director to its Board of Directors. Previously holding executive roles in global S&P 500 and Fortune 100 companies, Hughes brings a wealth of experience to the company. This appointment is effective immediately, signaling Allbirds' commitment to enhancing its board with top talent.

data.title: Agencia Comercial Spirits Ltd announces full exercise of underwriters' over-allotment option, raising gross proceeds to US$8.05 million.
data.description: On October 31, 2025, in Taichung City, Taiwan, Agencia Comercial Spirits Ltd (Nasdaq: AGCC), a company specializing in importing and distributing high-quality whiskies, disclosed that following its recent initial public offering which ended on October 23, 2025, the underwriters of the offering have fully exercised their over-allotment option. This entailed the purchase of an additional 262,500 Class A ordinary shares of the Company at US$4.00 per share, resulting in added gross proceeds totaling US$1.05 million, excluding underwriting discounts and offering expenses. The offering was executed on a firm commitment basis, with all Class A ordinary shares offered by Agencia.

data.title: ViaSat-3 F2 satellite to launch on Nov 5, 2025, aims to double network capacity, supporting new connectivity platforms.
data.description: Viasat's latest satellite, ViaSat-3 F2, is set to significantly boost the company's network capacity by more than doubling its current capabilities. This new satellite is tailored to propel customer expansion and support cutting-edge connectivity platforms like Viasat Amara, NexusWave, and Government Hybrid SATCOM Architecture. ViaSat-3 F2 aims to enhance services by catering to a wider clientele pool and is a vital step towards providing advanced connectivity solutions.

data.title: CareScout acquires Seniorly to aid families in elder care. Acquisition funded by Genworth with transition planning ahead.
data.description: In Richmond, Virginia, CareScout, a subsidiary of Genworth focused on aiding families through the aging process, has completed the acquisition of Seniorly, Inc., a prominent technology platform connecting families with senior living options. This acquisition, which was funded through Genworth’s holding company, will involve Seniorly, its advisor network, and partners shifting to the CareScout platform in the forthcoming months. This move is expected to enhance CareScout's resources and reach in assisting families with senior care solutions.

data.title: Peoples Financial Services Corp. (NASDAQ: PFIS) declares $0.6175/share dividend, payable on Dec 15, 2025.
data.description: In Scranton, Pennsylvania, on October 31, 2025, Peoples Financial Services Corp. announced a cash dividend for the fourth quarter, set at $0.6175 per share. Shareholders of record as of November 28, 2025, will receive the dividend on December 15, 2025. Peoples Financial Services Corp. is listed on NASDAQ under the symbol PFIS.

data.title: Otsuka ICU Medical LLC recalls 20 mEq Potassium Chloride Injection mislabeled as 10 mEq. Lot number: 1030613, Expiration Date: 09-30-2026.
data.description: In Austin, Texas, a voluntary recall has been initiated by Otsuka ICU Medical LLC for a mislabeled lot of POTASSIUM CHLORIDE Inj. 20 mEq, identified as NDC 0990-7077-14. The specific lot under recall is 1030613 with an Expiration Date of 09-30-2026. The overwrap label on this lot may contain incorrect information, prompting the recall. Consumers are advised to check their supplies and take necessary actions if they possess products from the affected lot.
